  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: Let It Be, Leave It Alone
---
So Cloud Chief got no answer. Three years later he was again traveling
east and, as he passed the fields of Sung, happened upon Big
Concealment once more. Cloud Chief, overjoyed, dashed forward and
presented himself, saying, "Heavenly Master, have you forgotten me?
Have you forgotten me?" Then he bowed his head twice and begged for
some instruction from Big Concealment.
